The accident involved two private vehicles, a Toyota Probox (L) and a Nissan AD (R). [Lydia Nyawira, Standard]  Four people died and two others critically injured following a head-on collision at Solio area in Kiawara, Nyeri County on the Nyeri-Nyahururu highway on Saturday.  The May 8 crash involved a Toyota Probox and a Nissan AD.  The AD, which had two occupants on board, was heading to Nyahururu from Nyeri, whereas the Probox, which had four occupants, was en route to Nyeri.  All the four occupants of the Toyota Probox died on the spot, police said. [Lydia Nyawira, Standard]  All the four occupants of the Probox died on the spot, Kieni West OCPD Ahmed Ali told The Standard.  “The Nissan AD had a tyre burst, resulting in the driver hurtling towards the oncoming traffic lane. The AD subsequently collided head-on with the Toyota Probox,” said Ali.  The injured occupants of the Nissan AD were taken to the Mary Immaculate Hospital Mweiga.  Take a quick survey and help us improve our website! The Nissan AD had a tyre burst, which led to the fatal crash. [Lydia Nyawira, Standard]  As of the time of publication, the mangled wreckages of the vehicles were still at the scene.     By Obare Osinde | 17 minutes ago By Brian Okoth | 4 hours ago By Robert Menza | 4 hours ago By Yvonne Chepkwony | 4 hours ago Read The Standard uninterrupted with no advertisements